Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the Software Engineer II role at Vitu. My recent experience building production systems across *Python*, *FastAPI*, *React Flow*, *TypeScript*, *Java*, *Spring Boot*, *PostgreSQL*, *Redis*, and *AWS* maps closely to the role's emphasis on building and maintaining software across multiple platforms, improving maintainability, and reducing technical debt. At Sperse, I helped ship a *multi-agent* CRM platform serving 10,000+ users, a client-facing workflow builder with durable execution, an *OpenAI Codex*-powered Bitbucket *MCP* review pipeline, and *GitHub Actions* *CI/CD* with *OpenTelemetry* evals to catch *latency*, *accuracy*, and *safety* issues before production. At Qualitest, I supported a cloud-agnostic storage service across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO*, tuned *PostgreSQL* for lower latency, and orchestrated 100K+ weekly jobs with *AWS Step Functions*.

What makes this opportunity a strong fit is the balance between product delivery and operational ownership. The Vitu role calls for thoughtful contributions to technical architecture, automated tests, troubleshooting, and ongoing application support; that is the same work pattern I have followed when building secure backend actions behind *FastMCP*, maintaining durable *Temporal* workflows, and keeping production systems observable through monitoring and trace-driven evaluation. I am comfortable working across client-facing web applications and backend services, and I enjoy turning stakeholder feedback into practical changes that improve reliability and user experience.

Vitu's mission to transform interactions between the private sector and government agencies, along with its employee-first culture of support and inclusion and collaborative, original approach, is exactly the kind of environment where I want to contribute. I would welcome the opportunity to help build software that makes vehicle and government workflows faster, clearer, and more dependable.

Thank you for your consideration.

